{"title": "Brain Twister", "description": "\"Mark Phillips\" is, or are, two writers: Randall Garrett and Laurence M. Janifer. Their joint pen-name, derived from their middle names (Philip and Mark), was coined soon after their original meeting, at a science-fiction convention. Both men were drunk at the time, which explains a good deal, and only one has ever sobered up. A matter for constant contention between the collaborators is which one.<br /><br />Originally published as That Sweet Little Old Lady, Brain Twister follows the adventures of FBI agent Kenneth J. Malone as he attempts to unravel the machinations of a telepathic spy.  His first problem: how do you find a telepath to catch the first telepath?<br /><br />The novella was nominated for the Hugo Award in 1960. (Summary from the text and Catharine Eastman)", "duration": 19099, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "6276", "name": "Randall Garrett"}, {"id": "1519", "name": "Laurence M. Janifer"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt15/Brain_Twister_1203.jpg", "copyright_year": "1962", "genres": ["Humorous Fiction", "Science Fiction", "Suspense", "Espionage", "Political & Thrillers"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Catharine Eastman"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Catharine Eastman"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Catharine Eastman"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Paul Williams"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Prologue", "readers": [83], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/brain_twister_ce_librivox/braintwister_00_phillips_64kb.mp3", "duration": 701}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 1", "readers": [83], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/brain_twister_ce_librivox/braintwister_01_phillips_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1782}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 2", "readers": [83], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/brain_twister_ce_librivox/braintwister_02_phillips_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3072}, {"section": 3, "title": "C